{"type":"message","id":"b613aeeb","parentId":"807a194c","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No apps registered yet. So Bobby needs to:\n1. Go to developer.x.com and create an app\n2. Then authenticate with xurl\n\nLet me explain the setup process to Bobby clearly.","thinkingSignature":"71ce675abf12777ab6c6aecf2f218c97cb883d41430a3cda03f3754862a46d78"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's how to get me set up with X API access:\n\n## Quick Overview\n\n**xurl** is already installed and supports everything you need — post, delete, reply, timeline, likes, reposts, etc.\n\n## Step 1: Create a Dev App\n\n1. Go to **[developer.x.com](https://developer.x.com)** → Dashboard → Create App\n2. Set permissions to **Read and Write**\n3. Go to **Keys and tokens** tab:\n   - Copy **API Key** and **API Key Secret**\n   - Generate **Access Token** and **Access Token Secret** (make sure it has Read+Write scope)\n\n## Step 2: Authenticate xurl\n\nOnce you have your credentials, you have two options:\n\n**Option A — OAuth1 (recommended for posting):**\n```bash\nxurl auth oauth1 --client-id YOUR_API_KEY --client-secret YOUR_API_KEY_SECRET --token YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN --token-secret YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET\n```\n\n**Option B — App-only (bearer token, read-only):**\n```bash\nxurl auth app --client-id YOUR_API_KEY --client-secret YOUR_API_KEY_SECRET --token YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN\n```\n\n## Step 3: Verify\n\n```bash\nxurl whoami\n```\n\n---\n\n**Which option is best for you?** If you just want me to read your feed and post content, OAuth1 with Read+Write access is what you need. Want me to set it up now when you have the credentials?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2863,"output":351,"cacheRead":26998,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30212,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777273637966,"responseId":"063e3e25b34d9637c6fa22f2f17590fd"}}
