{"type":"message","id":"57cfc84d","parentId":"82056c29","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.177Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking about setting up X (Twitter) API access so I can post, delete, and view his account. Let me check what the current setup is and what options are available.\n\nLooking at my SOUL.md, it says \"X API setup is pending\" under TOOLS.md notes. \n\nLet me check the xurl skill to understand how to set this up, and also check the current TOOLS.md for any existing X credentials.","thinkingSignature":"294445c92670640563c8bca817153868cd841c1a3c85f460ffbfc724066218e3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3uiyi57plhsr_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x/TOOLS.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3uiyi57plhsr_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/xurl/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":146,"output":166,"cacheRead":8391,"cacheWrite":18759,"totalTokens":27462,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777273607777,"responseId":"063e3e0825571a54c88c1d6166c9ddcf"}}
{"type":"message","id":"53c7cea5","parentId":"57cfc84d","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.178Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3uiyi57plhsr_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## X/Twitter\n- **Bobby's handle:** @bobbygalletta\n- **X API setup:** pending\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777273615344}}
