{"type":"message","id":"d82679a4","parentId":"d7e47be8","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `xurl` is installed at `/opt/homebrew/bin/xurl`. Let me check what it does and how to authenticate it.","thinkingSignature":"383c4b34ba9d4bbad177c841791ef197d70f66f66b8f51f6bc012af90b193ab4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0su41xgewrv0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl --help 2>&1 | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2010,"output":65,"cacheRead":26998,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29073,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777273628291,"responseId":"063e3e1c736e2ebbd314e5723e36bc89"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07383482","parentId":"d82679a4","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.179Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0su41xgewrv0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A command-line tool for making authenticated requests to the X API.\n\nShortcut commands (agent‑friendly):\n  xurl post \"Hello world!\"                        Post to X\n  xurl reply 1234567890 \"Nice!\"                   Reply to a post\n  xurl read 1234567890                             Read a post\n  xurl search \"golang\" -n 20                       Search posts\n  xurl whoami                                      Show your profile\n  xurl like 1234567890                             Like a post\n  xurl repost 1234567890                           Repost\n  xurl follow @user                                Follow a user\n  xurl dm @user \"Hey!\"                             Send a DM\n  xurl timeline                                    Home timeline\n  xurl mentions                                    Your mentions\n\nRaw API access (curl‑style):\n  basic requests        xurl /2/users/me\n                        xurl -X POST /2/tweets -d '{\"text\":\"Hello world!\"}'\n                        xurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" /2/tweets\n  authentication        xurl --auth oauth2 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth oauth1 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth app /2/users/me\n  media and streaming   xurl media upload path/to/video.mp4\n                        xurl /2/tweets/search/stream --auth app\n                        xurl -s /2/users/me\n\nMulti-app management:\n  xurl auth apps add my-app --client-id ... --client-secret ...\n  xurl auth apps list\n  xurl auth default                                # interactive picker\n  xurl auth default my-app                         # set by name\n  xurl --app my-app /2/users/me                    # per-request override\n\nRun 'xurl --help' to see all available commands.\n\nUsage:\n  xurl [flags] URL\n  xurl [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  auth        Authentication management\n  block       Block a user\n  bookmark    Bookmark a post\n  bookmarks   List your bookmarks\n  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell\n  delete      Delete a post\n  dm          Send a direct message\n  dms         List recent direct messages\n  follow      Follow a user\n  followers   List your followers"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":261,"aggregated":"A command-line tool for making authenticated requests to the X API.\n\nShortcut commands (agent‑friendly):\n  xurl post \"Hello world!\"                        Post to X\n  xurl reply 1234567890 \"Nice!\"                   Reply to a post\n  xurl read 1234567890                             Read a post\n  xurl search \"golang\" -n 20                       Search posts\n  xurl whoami                                      Show your profile\n  xurl like 1234567890                             Like a post\n  xurl repost 1234567890                           Repost\n  xurl follow @user                                Follow a user\n  xurl dm @user \"Hey!\"                             Send a DM\n  xurl timeline                                    Home timeline\n  xurl mentions                                    Your mentions\n\nRaw API access (curl‑style):\n  basic requests        xurl /2/users/me\n                        xurl -X POST /2/tweets -d '{\"text\":\"Hello world!\"}'\n                        xurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" /2/tweets\n  authentication        xurl --auth oauth2 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth oauth1 /2/users/me\n                        xurl --auth app /2/users/me\n  media and streaming   xurl media upload path/to/video.mp4\n                        xurl /2/tweets/search/stream --auth app\n                        xurl -s /2/users/me\n\nMulti-app management:\n  xurl auth apps add my-app --client-id ... --client-secret ...\n  xurl auth apps list\n  xurl auth default                                # interactive picker\n  xurl auth default my-app                         # set by name\n  xurl --app my-app /2/users/me                    # per-request override\n\nRun 'xurl --help' to see all available commands.\n\nUsage:\n  xurl [flags] URL\n  xurl [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  auth        Authentication management\n  block       Block a user\n  bookmark    Bookmark a post\n  bookmarks   List your bookmarks\n  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell\n  delete      Delete a post\n  dm          Send a direct message\n  dms         List recent direct messages\n  follow      Follow a user\n  followers   List your followers","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777273631789}}
{"type":"message","id":"579ad427","parentId":"07383482","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So xurl is installed and has a lot of functionality including post, reply, read, delete, timeline, etc. Let me check how to set up authentication with it.","thinkingSignature":"8db9e70bd14f63fe023ccc416e6d922ce16bdffa01d6156acead38928d761a7f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gmksh2die9v0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"xurl auth --help 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2556,"output":69,"cacheRead":26998,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29623,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777273631790,"responseId":"063e3e1f70ae859fcfb4401d8bba29a1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5aaa0c7e","parentId":"579ad427","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:07:31.179Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gmksh2die9v0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Authentication management\n\nUsage:\n  xurl auth [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  app         Configure app-auth (bearer token)\n  apps        Manage registered X API apps\n  clear       Clear authentication tokens\n  default     Set default app and/or user (interactive or by argument)\n  oauth1      Configure OAuth1 authentication\n  oauth2      Configure OAuth2 authentication\n  status      Show authentication status\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help   help for auth\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --app string   Use a specific registered app (overrides default)\n\nUse \"xurl auth [command] --help\" for more information about a command."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":38,"aggregated":"Authentication management\n\nUsage:\n  xurl auth [command]\n\nAvailable Commands:\n  app         Configure app-auth (bearer token)\n  apps        Manage registered X API apps\n  clear       Clear authentication tokens\n  default     Set default app and/or user (interactive or by argument)\n  oauth1      Configure OAuth1 authentication\n  oauth2      Configure OAuth2 authentication\n  status      Show authentication status\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help   help for auth\n\nGlobal Flags:\n      --app string   Use a specific registered app (overrides default)\n\nUse \"xurl auth [command] --help\" for more information about a command.","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-x"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777273634973}}
